  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "System Engineer",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Duties</strong></p><ul><li>Server Administration & Maintenance</li></ul><ul><li>Active Directory and Patch Management</li><li>Virtualization and Cloud Support</li><li>Security and Compliance</li><li>Backup and Disaster Recovery</li><li>Performance Monitoring and Automation</li><li>Troubleshooting and Escalations</li><li>Documentation and Knowledge Sharing</li></ul><p><br /><strong>Education & Professional Qualifications</strong></p><ul><li><p>Diploma or Bachelor’s degree in Information Technology, Computer Science, or a related discipline.</p></li><li><p>Relevant professional certifications (e.g. Microsoft, VMware, AWS, Azure, ITIL, CompTIA, or equivalent) will be an advantage.</p></li></ul><ul><li><p>Experience in server administration and maintenance in Windows and/or Linux environments.</p></li><li><p>Knowledge of Active Directory, Group Policy, and patch management processes.</p></li><li><p>Familiarity with virtualization platforms (e.g. VMware, Hyper-V) and cloud services (e.g. AWS, Azure, or GCP).</p></li><li><p>Understanding of IT security principles, compliance standards, and best practices.</p></li><li><p>Experience with backup, recovery, and disaster recovery solutions.</p></li><li><p>Ability to monitor system performance and implement automation or optimization tools.</p></li></ul>",
